					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Look at it like this:<br /><br />During T1, it loads BAL<br />During T2, it adds X to BAL, and loads BAH<br />During T3, it loads from BAH:(BAL+X)&amp;255, and adds the carry to BAH<br />- then, depending on whether there was a carry during T<strong>2</strong>, either it goes straight to T0 of the next opcode, or<br />During T4, it loads from (BAH+1):(BAL+X).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

