						<div class="postbody">This is a fairly good doc for cycle-by-cycle operation of instructions, although I believe it has some errors: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/6502_cpu.txt">http://nesdev.com/6502_cpu.txt</a><!-- m --> (see Absolute indexed addressing)<br /><br />Also note that 6502 is always reading or writing from memory on every cycle, this can't be turned off. It's usually safer to read from a semi-random address than write to it. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

					
